pped weapon; upgradeable to three pairs; two external pairs can be used to absorb hits but the whole pair will be lost)\n* Bomb (short-range, slow fire, area effect)\n* Laser (long-range)\n* Homing Missile (releases up to sixteen guided missiles) \n* Shield (invulnerability; lasts approx. 25 seconds, or 3 hits, whichever comes first; ends with audible warning)\n\nThe major weapons affect the enemies and terrain differently. For example, certain enemy towers can only be destroyed with Laser or Homing Missile; other enemies are destroyed ''much faster'' with specific weapons to match. If Bomb or Homing Missile are equipped, certain bonus targets will appear, or parts of the landscape may be destroyed to reveal bonuses. If Laser is active, certain plants in the landscape can be shot repeatedly to 'grow' and earn extra points until they scroll off-screen.\nIt has been reported that a bug in the game enabled the player to obtain all power-ups, simply by allowing themselves to be killed by the first enemy appearing upon starting the game without touching the controls. If this occurred, the next time the player ship appears, it has all the power-ups equipped.[http://www.rllmukforum.com/index.php?/topic/76529-best-trick-cheat-or-bug-in-an-arcade-game/page-2 Slap Fight bug]\n\n== Synopsis ==\n{{Expand section|date=March 2020}}\nTaking place in the year 2059 in another galaxy, mankind has colonized an alien planet called Theon after evacuating a previously colonized planet Orac. Five years ago, the colony on Orac was attacked by alien invaders and the war was so intense, the colonists were forced to leave. However, Theon is now under attack by the same alien fleet, but the humans are ready. The player assumes the role of an Allied League of Cosmic Nations (ALCON) fighter pilot in the SW475 star fighter to stop the invaders from taking over Theon.\n\n== Development ==\n{{Expand section|date=March 2020}}\n\n== Release ==\n{{Expand section|date=March 2020}}\nThe game was [[porting|ported]] to many 8-bit [[home computer]]s in the European & North American markets.\n\n''Slap Fight MD'' itself is a new game mode featuring featured new levels, graphics, weapons, music, etc., plus a new \"smart bomb\" feature at the cost of Wing powerups. The music for it was composed and arranged by [[Yuzo Koshiro]], which is presented on the title screen.\n\nThe original game was also included, but with changes such as configuration for the Shield's timer and an in-game announcer.\n\n=== Taito Nostalgia 2 version ===\n{{Expand section|date=March 2020}}\nIn ''Taito Nostalgia 2'' for Bandai's \"Let's! TV play CLASSIC\" series of plug-and-play game systems, the original Japanese version and a new ''Slap Fight Tiger'' are included.\n\nIn ''Slap Fight Tiger'', the player controls the Heli from ''[[Tiger Heli]]'' instead of the SW475. The laser is changed to fire in a 3-way forward spread. New enemies include the Invaders Army (from ''[[Space Invaders]]'').<ref>[http://archive.tamashii.jp/lyvp/play/t2slap2.html Taito Nostalgia 2 Slap Fight Tiger page] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130612113055/http://archive.tamashii.jp/lyvp/play/t2slap2.html |date=2013-06-12 }}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n{{Expand section|date=March 2020}}\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{moby game|id=/alcon|name=''Slap Fight''}}\n*[http://klov.com/game_detail.php?letter=&game_id=9583 ''Slap Fight'' entry] and also related [http://www.klov.com/game_detail.php?game_id=6843 ''Alcon'' entry] from the [[Killer List of Videogames|KLOV]]\n*{{WoS game|id=0004564}}\n\n{{Toaplan video games}}\n\n[[Category:Arcade games]]\n[[Category:Atari ST games]]\n[[Category:1986 video games]]\n[[Category:Sega Genesis games]]\n[[Category:Sega Genesis-only games]]\n[[Category:ZX Spectrum games]]\n[[Category:Commodore 64 games]]\n[[Category:Amstrad CPC games]]\n[[Category:Scrolling shooters]]\n[[Category:Toaplan games]]\n[[Category:Video games scored 